# Security Standards

## Never

- Commit secrets (`.env`, API keys, passwords, private keys)
- Log sensitive data (passwords, full account numbers, API keys)
- Use string concatenation for SQL — JPA/Hibernate parameterized queries only
- Expose stack traces in production API responses
- Run Docker containers as root in production configs

## Always

- Secrets via environment variables or Spring `@ConfigurationProperties`
- Validate all REST input with `@Valid` and Bean Validation
- Use HTTPS in production; restrict actuator endpoints
- Include `correlationId` in logs and Kafka headers (not PII)
- Pin dependency versions; run OWASP dependency-check in CI (Milestone 5)

## Security Review Trigger

When adding or modifying any of the following, invoke the **aiconomy-security** skill before merging:

- REST endpoints or auth
- Kafka topic handlers processing external input
- File or env configuration loading
- New Maven/PyPI dependencies
- Docker or deployment configs

See [.cursor/skills/aiconomy-security/SKILL.md](../skills/aiconomy-security/SKILL.md).
